      "comment": "CALIFORNIA FLYER (6) improved last start, beaten just 1.4L this track in trip after sitting forward. Recorded close to her best Victorian number, and the speedy galloper can break through. RAIDER'S OWN (5) fought on well for third last start over 1400m at this track, making it two minor placings this preparation. Has the inside barrier and a 1.5L claim and should be right in it. MONCLERE (4) has had plenty of chances but has pieces of form that would give him a chance. In the mix. LARAMANA (1) debuts and profiles well. Has an awkward gate but will be well prepared. MAY WE ALL (3) has come back to racing improved and can show more this preparation.",
